   "cell_type": "raw",
   "source": [
    "{\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Normalization Walkthrough on Synthetic Examples\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"This notebook shows exactly how each normalization choice changes text.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"It is useful for your report because it makes the design choices easy to justify.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"import pandas as pd\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from data_mining_assignment.tasks.preprocessing import NormalizationConfig, TextNormalizer\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Example inputs\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Each sample includes a different noise type:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- HTML tags\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- URL and email artifacts\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Symbol bursts and id-like codes\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"sample_texts = [\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"<p>Engine failure at STATION-44!!! urgent alert</p>\\\",\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"Visit https://bad-shop.example now and mail me@bad-shop.example\\\",\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"%%%% Buy now #### REF-8821 ####\\\",\\n\",\n",
    "    \"]\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"normalizer = TextNormalizer()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"bundle = normalizer.normalize_for_both_tasks(sample_texts)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"pd.DataFrame(\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    {\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"raw\\\": sample_texts,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"clustering_view\\\": bundle.clustering_texts,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"anomaly_view\\\": bundle.anomaly_texts,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    }\\n\",\n",
    "    \")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Custom config demo\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"You can tune the cleaning strategy per method.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"For example, this config keeps digits and symbols for anomaly detection but still removes HTML.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"custom_anomaly_config = NormalizationConfig(\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    preserve_structure_markers=True,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    remove_non_alphanumeric=False,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    remove_digits=False,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    use_lemmatization=False,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    use_stemming_fallback=False,\\n\",\n",
    "    \")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"custom_normalizer = TextNormalizer(anomaly_config=custom_anomaly_config)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"custom_bundle = custom_normalizer.normalize_for_both_tasks(sample_texts)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"pd.DataFrame({\\\"raw\\\": sample_texts, \\\"custom_anomaly_view\\\": custom_bundle.anomaly_texts})\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Report tip\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Use one table from this notebook in your PDF report to explain *why* two views are useful.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  }\n",
    " ],\n",
